  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic Tibial Tray CFD Credibility Assessment (NC-4 Clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a finite-element / CFD model predicting peak contact stress and subsurface strain in a tibial tray component of a total knee replacement system under physiological gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict relative stress distributions at Model Risk Level 3 to support design verification of a Class II orthopedic implant. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 3. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on material property inputs and boundary-condition magnitudes was performed. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that tibial bone modulus is the dominant input driver. Decision: Accepted.",
